rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<S1>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Stay safe, don’t damage the Field.{{/BOLD}} If, at any time, the {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} operation or {{LINK:#team}}Team{{/LINK}} actions are deemed unsafe or have damaged any Field Elements or {{LINK:#scoringobject}}Scoring Objects{{/LINK}}, the offending {{LINK:#team}}Team{{/LINK}} may be {{LINK:#disablement}}Disabled{{/LINK}} and/or {{LINK:#disqualification}}Disqualified{{/LINK}} at the {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee’s{{/LINK}} discretion. The {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} will require re-inspection before it may again take the {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}}.
 Note: {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} may not step onto the {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}} at any time. If a {{LINK:#team}}Team’s{{/LINK}} {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} requires stepping onto the {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}} during pre-{{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}} setup, this will be considered a {{LINK:#violation}}Violation{{/LINK}} of <S1>, <GG3>, and/or <SG1>. The {{LINK:#team}}Team’s{{/LINK}} {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} may be removed from the current {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}} at the {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee’s{{/LINK}} discretion.

{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}Violation Notes: {{LINK:#majorviolation}}Major Violations{{/LINK}} should be reported to and/or discussed with the {{LINK:#eventpartner}}Event Partner{{/LINK}} during the event, and should be reported to the REC Foundation Rules and Conduct Committee following the event.{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

