rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<GG9>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Don’t damage the Field.{{/BOLD}} {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} interactions which damage the {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}} or any Field Elements are prohibited. For the purpose of this rule, “damage” is defined as anything which requires repair in order to begin the next {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}, such as causing part of a {{LINK:#goal}}Goal{{/LINK}} to detach from the {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}}.
  {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} are responsible for the actions of their {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} at all times, especially when interacting with the {{LINK:#goal}}Goals{{/LINK}}. If a {{LINK:#team}}Team{{/LINK}} chooses to repeatedly ram full-speed into a {{LINK:#fieldelements}}Field Element{{/LINK}}, it will be hard to convince a {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee{{/LINK}} that any damage caused was “accidental.”


{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}Violation Notes:{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

• In most cases, accidental {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}} damage should only be considered a {{LINK:#minorviolation}}Minor Violation{{/LINK}}
• Egregious, intentional, or repeated accidental/{{LINK:#minorviolation}}Minor Violations{{/LINK}} may escalate to a {{LINK:#majorviolation}}Major Violation{{/LINK}} at the {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee’s{{/LINK}} discretion

